<dl>
<dd>They should be edited. However people don&#39;t always do so.<a href="" title="User:Geni">Geni</a> 10:19, 10 May 2009 (UTC)</dd></dl>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Heritage_categories_.28revisited.29">Heritage categories (revisited)</span></h2>

<p>There is an existing policy, found at <a href="#Heritage" title="Wikipedia:Naming conventions (categories)">Wikipedia:Naming conventions (categories)</a>.  Earlier in the history of Wikipedia, we spent over 6 months hammering out a clear and concise policy. It was ignored by random editors that don&#39;t bother to read and understand policy. Over 2 more years at <a href="" title="WP:CfD">WP:CfD</a>, a better compromise form was adopted after much discussion (and I was not involved).</p>
<p><b>Fooian Barians</b> has been replaced by <i>&#34;<b>Fooian</b> people of <b>Barian</b> descent&#34;</i> for clarity.</p>
<p>The older policy wasn&#39;t easily workable and readily apparent in practice. Folks had difficulty distinguishing adjectival usage. Many names simply are unworkable in either <i>Fooian Barians</i> or <i>Fooian-Barians</i> forms (such as, &#34;Puerto Rican&#34;, &#34;Dominican Republic&#34;, &#34;Saint Vincent and the Grenadines&#34;).</p>
<p>The updated policy prevents arguments, and long, slow motion, edit wars using   between hyphenated and unhyphenated forms. All to the good!</p>
<p>Over time and much discussion, all of the subcategories of <a href="" title="Category:People by ethnic or national descent">Category:People by ethnic or national descent</a> have been updated to this new form. All of the subcategories of most nationalities have been updated to this new form. For example,
</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="" title="Category:People of British descent">Category:People of British descent</a></li>
<li><a href="" title="Category:British people by ethnic or national origin">Category:British people by ethnic or national origin</a></li>
<li><a href="" title="Category:People of Canadian descent">Category:People of Canadian descent</a></li>
<li><a href="" title="Category:Canadian people by ethnic or national origin">Category:Canadian people by ethnic or national origin</a></li></ol>

<p>Some American subcategories have been updated.  For example, <a href="#Category:Polish-Americans" title="Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2008 June 29">Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2008 June 29</a>. Now, there are some editors (having lost the previous debate) that want to change back at <a href="#Category:Americans_of_Polish_descent" title="Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2009 May 3">Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2009 May 3</a>.</p>
<p>See also <a href="#Category:Turkish_Americans" title="Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2009 May 2">Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2009 May 2</a>, where an editor surreptitiously used category redirect to reverse repeated CfD decisions at:
</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="#Category:Turkish-Americans" title="Wikipedia:Categories for deletion/Log/2006 July 25">Wikipedia:Categories for deletion/Log/2006 July 25</a></li>
<li><a href="#Category:Turkish-Americans" title="Wikipedia:Categories for deletion/Log/2006 August 3">Wikipedia:Categories for deletion/Log/2006 August 3</a></li>
<li><a href="#American_people_by_ethnic_or_national_origin" title="Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2007 February 8">Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2007 February 8</a></li></ol>

<p>Please join the discussion, and help end <a href="" title="American exceptionalism">American exceptionalism</a>.&#60;br /&#62;--<a href="" title="User:William Allen Simpson">William Allen Simpson</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:William Allen Simpson">talk</a>) 03:56, 6 May 2009 (UTC)</p>

<ul>
<li><b>Proposed Compromise</b> -- rather than debating these case by case, and Cydebot surreptitiously making changes without a CfD (as it did for Jewish-American activists→Jewish American activists), could we develop a comprehensive American guideline?
<ol>
<li>All multiple word ethnicities in the now standard form: <a href="" title="Category:American people of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines descent">Category:American people of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines descent</a>.</li>
<li>All generic ethnicity parent categories without hyphen: <a href="" title="Category:African American people">Category:African American people</a>, <a href="" title="Category:Native American people">Category:Native American people</a>.</li>
<li>All single word national ethnicity nouns without hyphen: <a href="" title="Category:Turkish Americans">Category:Turkish Americans</a>.</li>
<li>Any single word national ethnicity adjectives must have hyphen, even though the parent category and main article have no hyphen: <a href="" title="Category:Polish-American musicians">Category:Polish-American musicians</a>.</li></ol>
<dl>
<dd>Will folks enforce these in the future without exception? Otherwise, the bickering will continue.&#60;br /&#62;--<a href="" title="User:William Allen Simpson">William Allen Simpson</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:William Allen Simpson">talk</a>) 16:10, 7 May 2009 (UTC)</dd></dl></li></ul>


<ul>
<li>Number 2 is not entirely logical. If African American is parallel to Native American, then African is parallel to Native. <a href="" title="User:Peter jackson">Peter jackson</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:Peter jackson">talk</a>) 17:07, 7 May 2009 (UTC)
<ul>
<li>That&#39;s how they (mostly  , mostly late last year) seems to have set them up, all at the same level, along with Native Hawaiian, Alaska Native, Black African, European American, Latin American, etc.... Compare <a href="" title="Category:American people by ethnic or national origin">Category:American people by ethnic or national origin</a> with <a href="" title="Category:People by ethnic or national descent">Category:People by ethnic or national descent</a>. While I may not entirely agree with it, that&#39;s the current arrangement. &#60;nowiki&#62;&#60;sarcasm&#62;&#60;/nowiki&#62;Wasn&#39;t it thoroughly discussed here in advance?&#60;nowiki&#62;&#60;/sarcasm&#62;&#60;/nowiki&#62;&#60;br /&#62;--<a href="" title="User:William Allen Simpson">William Allen Simpson</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:William Allen Simpson">talk</a>) 00:30, 8 May 2009 (UTC)</li></ul></li></ul>


<ul>
<li>Extended discussion at two more places:
<ul>
<li><a href="#Naming_conventions" title="Category talk:American people by ethnic or national origin">Category talk:American people by ethnic or national origin</a></li>
<li><a href="#European_Americans" title="Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2009 May 11">Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2009 May 11</a></li></ul>
