<ul>
<li>&#34;Material from mainstream news organizations is welcomed, particularly the high-quality end of the market, for example the <b>Washington Post</b> in the United States and <b>the Times</b> in Britain, as well as widely used conglomerates such as the <b>Associated Press</b>.&#34;</li></ul>

<p>1) Should we also mention OED in the policy?
AND/OR
2) Should we say something about dictionaries? (Currently, dictionaries arent mentioned).</p>
<p>I&#39;m proposing this cause I&#39;ve run into a problem here <a href="#OED" title="Talk:Fascism">Talk:Fascism</a> and it seems to be a very redundant problem so if we make the policy clearer, noone in the future would have to run into a similar problem. <a href="" title="User:Phoenix of9">Phoenix of9</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:Phoenix of9">talk</a>) 16:35, 28 May 2009 (UTC)</p>

<dl>
<dd>
<dl>
